    <!-- Help -->

    <string name="help_mortgage_type_info"><b><i>Select mortgage type</i></b>
        \n\n<b><i>FRM Constant loan payments</i></b>
        \nFixed rate mortgage, in which the monthly payment (interest plus principal) is constant over the loan term. Interest rate is fixed. Most popular amortization schedule.
        \n\n<b><i>FRM Constant principal payments</i></b>
        \nFixed rate mortgage, in which the principal paid, not the total monthly payment, remains constant. Total monthly payments
        decrease due to decreasing monthly interest. Interest rate is fixed. The first monthly payments are higher than in the case of a constant loan payments 
        loan, but the total payment is lower (less total interest needs to be paid).
        \n\n<b><i>ARM Adjustable Rate Mortgage</i></b>
        \nA mortgage loan in which the interest rate paid on the outstanding balance is periodically adjusted according to a specific index. The initial interest rate is usually
         fixed for a period of time (adjustment period) after which it is reset every few months.
        </string>

    <string name="help_mortgage_name_info"><b><i>Mortgage name</i></b>
        \nYour chosen name that identifies a specific mortgage.
        </string>

    <string name="help_purchase_price_info"><b><i>Purchase price</i></b>
        \nPrice of the purchased property.
        </string>

    <string name="help_down_payment_info" formatted="false"><b><i>Down payment</i></b>
        \nAmount that you will pay in cash at the onset of the loan. Many banks require that it amounts to 20% of the purchase price.
        </string>
    
    <string name="help_mortgage_term_info"><b><i>Mortgage term</i></b>
        \nThe length of time the mortgage terms and conditions (including interest rate) are in effect.
        </string>
    
    <string name="help_interest_rate_info"><b><i>Interest rate</i></b>
        \nAnnual interest rate (nominal) on the mortgage.
        </string>
    
    <string name="help_home_insurance_info"><b><i>Home insurance</i></b>
        \nAnnual insurance against risks to the property (hazard insurance, homeowner\'s insurance).
        </string>
    
    <string name="help_property_tax_info"><b><i>Property tax</i></b>
        \nAnnual tax on the bought property.
        </string>

    <string name="help_pmi_info"><b><i>PMI</i></b>
        \nAnnual Private Mortgage Insurance, paid to the lender if the down payment is lower than 20\u0025 of the purchased property price or when the loan-to-value ratio is lower than 80\u0025. Loan-to-value ratio is a ratio of the loan to the value of an asset purchased. It is an annual percentage of loan amount.
        </string>

    <string name="help_closing_fees_info"><b><i>Closing fees</i></b>
        \nThe total of one-time fees (attorney, survey, application fees, etc.).
        </string>

    <string name="help_extra_payment_info"><b><i>Extra payment</i></b>
        \nMonthly or yearly additional principal payment that reduces the costs and term of the loan. Yearly amount will be divided by 12 months and added
        to the monthly principal payment.
        </string>

    <string name="help_adjustment_radio_buttons_info"><b><i>Adjustment strategy for ARM</i></b>
        \n\n<b>7\//1</b> Fixed for 84 months, adjusts annually for the remaining part of the loan.
        \n\n<b>5\//1</b> Fixed for 60 months, adjusts annually for the remaining part of the loan.
        \n\n<b>3\//1</b> Fixed for 36 months, adjusts annually for the remaining part of the loan.
        \n\n<b>other</b> You can specify how many months the initial interest rate is fixed (<i>Adjustment period</i>) and how often the interest rate will be 
        adjusted after this period (<i>Between adjustments</i>).
        </string>
    
    <string name="help_adjustment_period_info"><b><i>Adjustment period</i></b>
        \nThe number of months during which the initial interest rate is not changed. After this period the periodic adjustments will begin.
        This number cannot be higher than the total number of payment months.
        </string>

    <string name="help_months_between_adjustments_info"><b><i>Months between adjustments</i></b>
        \nThe number of months (payments) between the adjustments. 12 means the adjustment is annual.
        </string>

    <string name="help_max_single_rate_adjustment_info" formatted="false"><b><i>Single adjustment rate</i></b>
        \nThe expected rate by which the interest rate will change periodically. This amount will be added to the previous interest rate.
        Eg. if the initial interest rate is 5% and a single adjustment is 0.25%, the rate after the 1st adjustment will be 5.25%, the next one will be 5.50%, and so on. 
        </string>
        
    <string name="help_total_interest_cap_info"><b><i>Total interest cap</i></b>
        \nA maximum interest rate that will not be exceeded. Once the rate is adjusted to the cap, it remains at this level until the loan is paid off.

        </string>
            
    <string name="help_general">
        \n\n<b>Loan amount</b>\nValue of the loan (purchase price - downpayment)
        \n\n<b># of payments</b>\nThe total number of payments to pay off the loan amount.
        \n\nCompounding is monthly.
        \nMax number of mortgages stored is 30.
        \nMax number of mortgages to compare is 6.
        </string>
        
